<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Salix</i> <i>planifolia</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Salix</i> <i>eastwoodiae</i>, <i>Salix</i> <i>orestera</i> and <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>cespitosum</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 3 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is variable with a diversity of upper-elevation, wet meadow species. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Subalpine wet or saturated streamsides, tarn edges, and wet meadows. Soils are alluvial and derived from granitic parent materials. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Salix planifolia</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

		
